tetrology
--12/2011

by Joe Hay

LICENSE: All files contained here are open-source software released under the terms of the GPL (http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl.html).

tetrology is a Four-in-a-Line game I developed as a practice exercise when studying John Zelle's book, "Python Programming: An introduction to Computer Science."

The program consists of 7 files:

Two graphics modules developed by John Zelle for his text:
-graphics.py
-button.py

The tetrology files.
-tetroboard.py
-tetrobutton.py
-tetrogui.py
-tetroinfo.py
-tetrology.py           - This one runs the program